 the military, or mediated and changed by cultural practices and memory. Building on recent scholarship in sound studies and affect theory, Heller questions not only how sound propagates acoustically but how sonic presences temper our total experience of the world around us.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMusicxAcoustics and physics2DLC. 0aMusicxAcoustics and physics. 0aPsychoacoustics2DLC. 0aPsychoacoustics. 0aSound2DLC. 0aSound. 7aMUSIC / Genres & Styles / Opera.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079134140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520975866?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520975866423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520975866/original  a978-3-11-079134-1  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_EMB  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles